@page "/privacy-policy"

<div class="policy-wrapper">
    <div class="policy-card">
        <div class="policy-header">
            <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="20" fill="#5B2D8A" />
                <path d="M29 17H26V15C26 13.9 26.9 13 28 13H29V10H26C23.8 10 22 11.8 22 14V17H19V20H22V30H26V20H28.6L29 17Z" fill="white" />
            </svg>
            <div>
                <h1 class="policy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="policy-meta">CNU Facebook Manager &nbsp;|&nbsp; Effective from January 1, 2025</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section>
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                CNU Facebook Manager ("the Application") is a tool developed by Chalermkarnchana University (CNU) to help Facebook page administrators
                manage messages and automated replies efficiently. We place great importance on user privacy and data related to your Facebook page.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>2. Data We Access</h2>
            <p>When you connect your Facebook account to the Application, we request access to the following data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Basic profile information</strong> — Username and publicly visible profile picture</li>
                <li><strong>List of Facebook pages</strong> — Pages you have permission to manage</li>
                <li><strong>Inbox messages</strong> — Messages sent by users to your page, used to process automated replies</li>
                <li><strong>Page token</strong> — Used to send reply messages on behalf of your page</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3. Purpose of Data Use</h2>
            <p>We use the data we access only for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Display the list of Facebook pages you have permission to manage within the Application</li>
                <li>Send and receive messages on behalf of your page, for the AI auto-reply function</li>
                <li>Store the page token so the system can operate continuously</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We do not sell, share, or use this data for marketing purposes.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Page tokens are stored, encrypted, in a database on servers controlled by CNU</li>
                <li>Messenger messages are processed in real time and message content is not stored permanently</li>
                <li>The system uses HTTPS for all communication channels</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>5. Sharing Data with Third Parties</h2>
            <p>
                We do not share your data with third parties, except where necessary to send data to the Facebook API
                as part of the normal operation of the Meta platform, which is governed by the
                <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Privacy Policy</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>6. User Rights</h2>
            <p>You may:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Disconnect the Application at any time via <strong>Facebook Settings → Apps and Websites</strong></li>
                <li>Request that your data be deleted from the system by contacting us at the email below</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>7. Data Deletion</h2>
            <p>
                If you wish to delete all data associated with your account, please contact us at
                <a href="mailto:cnuprogrammer2021@gmail.com">cnuprogrammer2021@gmail.com</a>
                We will process your request within 30 business days.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                If there are significant changes to this policy, we will notify you through the Application.
                Continued use of the Application after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact:<br />
                <strong>CNU Facebook Manager</strong><br />
                Email: <a href="mailto:cnuprogrammer2021@gmail.com">cnuprogrammer2021@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
        </section>

        <div class="policy-footer">
            <a href="/" class="text-muted text-decoration-none small">&larr; Back to home</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .policy-wrapper {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 32px 16px 48px;
    }

    .policy-card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 16px;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
        padding: 40px 48px;
    }

    .policy-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 32px;
        padding-bottom: 24px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #f0f0f0;
    }

    .policy-title {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #5B2D8A;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .policy-meta {
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: #888;
        margin: 4px 0 0;
    }

    section {
        margin-bottom: 28px;
    }

    section h2 {
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #333;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    section p, section li {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    section ul {
        padding-left: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    section a {
        color: #5B2D8A;
    }

    .policy-footer {
        margin-top: 32px;
        padding-top: 20px;
        border-top: 1px solid #f0f0f0;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 600px) {
        .policy-card { padding: 24px 20px; }
        .policy-header { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; }
    }
</style>
